investigated.

The expressions for the Born () and the ultraviolet
approximation () can be evaluated straightforwardly. For the
infrared () and the modified infrared approach ()
the few first terms of the infinite series representations suffice for
obtaining an accurate result. The integrals for the Abelian approximation
have to be handled with standard numerical methods. The exact solution
requires the handling of path-ordered exponentials and subsequent
integrations. 

 
 
 
